I had trouble getting this to play on my laptop,(C2D 1.83Ghz, 2GB RAM,XP)which already had ffdshow, media player classic and vlc media player amongst other things. I was getting 50% dropped frames. I then downloaded and installed a K-Lite Codec Pack/Media Player Classic combo installer (7MB from TPB) and that purged all the old stuff and sorted things. No dropped frames now, perfect! So if you're having similar problems, I'd recommend the re-install and clean up. Don't blame it on slicknick!
